cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.EC 

This paper deals with fair division among strategic agents and uses algorithmic approaches to design protocols that guarantee fairness. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses computational frameworks and subgame perfect Nash equilibria, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of cake cutting, which is a classic problem in economics and falls under the category of computational economics (cs.EC).
